name: Event/Component Category (P1)
description: The main category or component an Interaction belongs to, e.g. "Suggested Search", "Filter", etc...

name: Event Action/Cause (P2)
description: What is causing an Event (e.g. a click on a suggested search result) - sometimes also simply used to further detail an Event (to remain aligned with GA)

name: Event Label (P3)
description: A readable description of an Event - sometimes also simply used to further detail an Event (to remain aligned with GA)

name: Event/Component Sub-Category (P4)
description: A variable to detail an interaction with a component. The meaning depends on the Component/Event Category.

name: Component Aspect 1 (P5)
description: A variable to detail an interaction with a component. The meaning depends on the Component/Event Category.

name: Component Aspect 2 (P6)
description: A variable to detail an interaction with a component. The meaning depends on the Component/Event Category.

name: Component ID (P7)
description: Allows to distinguish several types of the same component on one page (e.g. several teaser boxes)

name: Component Location (P8)
description: Location where an interaction with a component happened (e.g. footer, header etc.)

name: Component Inner Location (P9)
description: The location inside of a component where an interaction happened (e.g. the position of a teaser within a teaser grid component)

name: User Purchase History - per Hit (P11)
description: Purchase History of a User (to identify Repeat Buyers)

name: Internal Search - Clicked Result Position (P13)
description: The Position the internal Search Result had which was clicked

name: Internal Search Result Count (P14)
description: Number of Results in the Internal Search

name: Internal Search Term (P15)
description: Internal Search Term - Use for Pathing and Hit-based correlations

name: Page Title (P17)
description: The HTML Page Title, shortened to the first 100 characters

name: Site Section as Prop (P18)
description: The Site Section (Page Category) as prop to allow Pathing Reports.

name: Clean URL (P19) - 100 char
description: max 100 char - use for pathing reports only. For others, use the corresponding V variable (e.g. P1 => V1)

name: Full URL (P20) - debugging - 100 char
description: max 100 char - use for pathing reports only. For others, use the corresponding V variable (e.g. P1 => V1)

name: URL Hostname (P21) - 100 char
description: max 100 char - use for pathing reports only. For others, use the corresponding V variable (e.g. P1 => V1)

name: URL Pathname (P22) - 100 char
description: max 100 char - use for pathing reports only. For others, use the corresponding V variable (e.g. P1 => V1)

name: Full URL Query String (P23) - 100 char
description: max 100 char - use for pathing reports only. For others, use the corresponding V variable (e.g. P1 => V1)

name: URL Pathname + Clean Query String (P24) - 100 char
description: max 100 char - use for pathing reports only. For others, use the corresponding V variable (e.g. P1 => V1)

name: URL Hash (P25) - 100 char
description: max 100 char - use for pathing reports only. For others, use the corresponding V variable (e.g. P1 => V1)

name: Referrer of Current Page (P26) - 100 char
description: max 100 char - use for pathing reports only. For others, use the corresponding V variable (e.g. P1 => V1)

name: Clean URL Query String (P27) - 100 chars
description: max 100 char - use for pathing reports only. For others, use the corresponding V variable (e.g. P1 => V1)

name: Event:Path+Clean QueryStr (P28)
description: Shows the Event Type (Event Category/"P" for Pageview) plus Pathname+Clean Query String for any Hit (Pageview or Event) and thus allows Pathing for Event and Pageview Hits.

name: Event:Pathname (P29)
description: Shows the Event Type (Event Category/"P" for Pageview) plus Pathname for any Hit (Pageview or Event) and thus allows Pathing for Event and Pageview Hits.

name: Siroop ID (Unique Customer ID, ucid) (P30)
description: Unique Contact ID starting with resiroop. Only fallback. Use V30 prioritarily.

name: Weekday (P32)
description: Day of the Week from Sunday to Saturday (1=Sunday, 7=Saturday). Available since 1/29/2016

name: Date (YYYYMMDD) (P33)
description: Full Date in format YYYMMDD - available since April 22, 2016

name: Client ID (P35) - formerly Device ID
description: The value of the Client ID Cookie (general User Cookie) - earlier called "Device ID"

name: Reg. User ID (P36)
description: The value of the Reg. User ID Cookie "siroid"

name: Login Status (P37)
description: y = user was logged in during this hit, n = user was not logged in

name: Payment Type of Completed Order (P38)
description: Payment Type of an Order, tracked when order is completed only

name: Transaction ID (P40) - debugging only
description: Transaction ID as a prop - use for debugging purposes only, otherwise use V40

name: Cart Value (P50)
description: Value in the shopping cart (since 3/6/2016). Only measured from the cart onwards.

name: Product List Name - Views & Clicks (P55)
description: Name of Product Lists a user viewed or clicked. Multiple lists per page possible. Not to be confused with Product Display Context (V55). Be carefule when using with Product Dimensions (for clicke, V75 is the best solution)

name: Order Voucher Codes: Descr (P56-List)
description: Voucher Codes: Descr used in an order (scheme voucherid/vouchername)

name: User ZIP Code (P60)
description: User Zip Code. Is gathered in Checkout.

name: User Gender (P61)
description: User Gender. Is gathered in Checkout.

name: User Age (P62)
description: User Age. Is gathered in Checkout.

name: Hit: Campaign ID (P70) - pathing only
description: Ignore for any analysis besides Pathing. Contains the Campaign ID as a prop, e.g. for Pathing Analysis

name: TV Spot Start (P73)
description: Timestamp of the time when TV Spot started

name: Error Type (P74)
description: Type of the Error

name: Error Value (P75)
description: Error description. List variable (allows to send multiple values in one hit)
